{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/how-to-preview-a-readme-with-github-styles/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>After trying a lot of tools there’s only one that have worked flawlessly for me. It’s a Python module called <a href=\"https://github.com/joeyespo/grip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">grip</a>.</p>\n<h1>Installation</h1>\n<p>You can either install it using <a href=\"https://brew.sh/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Homebrew</a> (<strong>recommended</strong>) or Python.</p>\n<h2>Homebrew</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> grip</code></pre></div>\n<p><em>You can skip to the Usage section now</em>.</p>\n<h2>Python</h2>\n<p>I normally recommend using <a href=\"https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/latest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">virtualenvs</a> to install anything in Python. Install that along with <a href=\"https://virtualenvwrapper.readthedocs.io/en/latest/command_ref.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">virtualenvwrapper</a>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>List your virtualenvs</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ lsvirtualenv\nmyenv\n<span class=\"token operator\">==</span><span class=\"token operator\">==</span>\nbar\n<span class=\"token operator\">==</span><span class=\"token operator\">==</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Activate one environment</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ workon myenv\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>myenv<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> $</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Install <code class=\"language-text\">grip</code></li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>myenv<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> $ pip <span class=\"token function\">install</span> grip</code></pre></div>\n<h1>Usage</h1>\n<p>To render the readme of a repository:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ cd my-repo\n$ grip\n * Running on http://localhost:6419/</code></pre></div>\n<p>To render a specific markdown file:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ grip CONTRIBUTE.md\n * Running on http://localhost:6419/</code></pre></div>\n<p>Open your browser at <code class=\"language-text\">http://localhost:6419</code>. Profit.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 662px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/9dbdb/reminders.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.0722891566265%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"screenshot for reminders github readme\"\n        title=\"screenshot for reminders github readme\"\n        src=\"/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/be86f/reminders.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/e72ac/reminders.png 166w,\n/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/62452/reminders.png 331w,\n/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/be86f/reminders.png 662w,\n/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/0f7d5/reminders.png 993w,\n/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/eb2ef/reminders.png 1324w,\n/static/7ed45a2ed47b9ac85a81342683b62b68/9dbdb/reminders.png 2622w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>API Limits</h1>\n<p>Grip uses the Github API directly to render the markdown files. This is fine until you hit the 60 API requests / min limit. From there, you can use basic auth to increase the limit to 5000 requests / min:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ grip --user johndoe --pass foobarbaz</code></pre></div>\n<p>Or, you can just use the VSCode markdown previewer for a while until you get access to Github again. Click on the top-right icon with the glass to preview the markdown.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 662px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/c679a/preview-button.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.81927710843374%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Preview button in VSCode\"\n        title=\"Preview button in VSCode\"\n        src=\"/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/be86f/preview-button.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/e72ac/preview-button.png 166w,\n/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/62452/preview-button.png 331w,\n/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/be86f/preview-button.png 662w,\n/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/0f7d5/preview-button.png 993w,\n/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/eb2ef/preview-button.png 1324w,\n/static/329a457e668e805698728d5aafe92c44/c679a/preview-button.png 2460w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>And this how it looks like:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 662px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/b2313/vscode-preview.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.036144578313255%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"VSCode preview\"\n        title=\"VSCode preview\"\n        src=\"/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/be86f/vscode-preview.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/e72ac/vscode-preview.png 166w,\n/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/62452/vscode-preview.png 331w,\n/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/be86f/vscode-preview.png 662w,\n/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/0f7d5/vscode-preview.png 993w,\n/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/eb2ef/vscode-preview.png 1324w,\n/static/8aac59ee6b584285a475b24a0c6c91b3/b2313/vscode-preview.png 2700w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to preview a README with GitHub styles","description":"Use Python to preview markdowns as rendered in GitHub","meta":"In this post I'll show how to preview markdown files, like README.md, before pushing the code to master. It's useful to write documentations and preview them before going live on GitHub.","date":"April 15, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-preview-a-readme-with-github-styles/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/quarantine/quarantine-day-26/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Quarantine — Day 26"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/please-stop-doing-this-in-your-resume/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Please stop doing this in your resume"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864","63159454"]}